{"TopicId":159516,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Perpetuum mobile possible with KSP ?","CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T23:40:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T23:40:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan it be done ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked for posts about this on the forum but found 0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny thoughts or ideas about this ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"W. Kerman","CreatedById":166763,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T23:45:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223028567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492731622\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145841\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Triop\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Triop said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan it be done ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked for posts about this on the forum but found 0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny thoughts or ideas about this ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerpetual motion you mean?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, RTGs have infinite power, and a reaction wheel would turn that into motion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoom. Broke physics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(\u0027course, physics isn\u0027t like that in real life.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T00:01:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223028573\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492731946\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166763\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022W. Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, W. Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerpetual motion you mean?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, RTGs have infinite power, and a reaction wheel would turn that into motion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoom. Broke physics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(\u0027course, physics isn\u0027t like that in real life.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Google translate **** with me....\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u0026lt;_\u0026lt;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_dry.png\u0022 title=\u0022\u0026lt;_\u0026lt;\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut searching for Perpetual motion on this forum also says 0...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it is possible (even with mods, not counting full rewriting of cfg files.), \u003Cstrong\u003Ewhere are all the machines ? \u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncould you build one, just for example ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-21T00:01:56Z\u0022 title=\u002204/21/2017 12:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Triop\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wadusher0","CreatedById":105513,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T00:57:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223028567\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492731622\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145841\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Triop\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Triop said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan it be done ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked for posts about this on the forum but found 0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny thoughts or ideas about this ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell there is this crazy contraption by Scott Manley that creates endless thrust by pumping ore around 2 spinning beams with 4 ore tanks... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/_AKdTj5Pgvs?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nObviously it requires some mods to work - notably Infernal Robotics and kOS - but he\u0027s demonstrated the fundamental physics deficiency he used\u00A0with stock parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, if you google Kraken Drive, you\u0027ll see all sorts of physics abusing monstrosities that\u0027ll fly wherever you want for free. Needless to say, there\u0027s a lot of insane exploits within the physics engine.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-21T01:08:04Z\u0022 title=\u002204/21/2017 01:08  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by wadusher1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T01:11:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223028650\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492736255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174571\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wadusher1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, wadusher1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell there is this crazy contraption by Scott Manley that creates endless thrust by pumping ore around 2 spinning beams with 4 ore tanks... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for making me feel even more stupid then I was, just watched Scott\u0027s video and I didn\u0027t understand any of it...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022^_^\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022^_^\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T02:17:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223028664\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159516\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492737091\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145841\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Triop\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Triop said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0just watched Scott\u0027s video and I didn\u0027t understand any of it...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry this one, he explains it well: \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Lnvh08GBOII?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T02:25:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe reason I asked was I made this contraption:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kquNwWR.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/kquNwWR.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sdfE7LL.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sdfE7LL.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow I\u0027ve made a probe with reaction wheels and when I release it in the tunnel and turn the vessel it will go forward on its own, not using power.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis can go on forever, but it is slow...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaking a perpetudinges that would pick up speed would be awesome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: I should make a video...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-21T02:26:44Z\u0022 title=\u002204/21/2017 02:26  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Triop\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T03:04:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCertainly you can get up to shenanigans with reaction wheels, as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166763-w-kerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022166763\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166763-w-kerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@W. Kerman\u003C/a\u003E points out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack in the day, I managed to build a functional fully-electric whirlybird, entirely stock, powered by reaction wheels; it could fly up to (IIRC) around 20 km altitude...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022OVduL0h.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/OVduL0h.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...That was in 0.90, though.\u00A0 No idea if it would still work in 1.2.2.\u00A0 Aside from the KSP aero model being different back then, it also relied on \u0022massless parts\u0022 being truly massless and dragless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I wouldn\u0027t be at all surprised if some form of reaction-wheel whirlybird were still possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Numerlor","CreatedById":174198,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T05:42:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made this a while ago, maybe you could get it to fly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/159022-spin-without-input/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3017323\u0026amp;embedComment=3017323\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3017323\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-21T13:31:21Z\u0022 title=\u002204/21/2017 01:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Numerlor\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reusables","CreatedById":179182,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-21T05:55:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made one on 1.2, to test if electric tiltwing\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E is possible. This one only has the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022afoXbpE.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/afoXbpE.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I remember correctly, this one got to 8km. Without the heavy crew cabins, it could get to 25km~30km and get broken(this was\u00A0typical test routine of my electric propellers).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbandoned it as it was hard to control.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: You can find more of these\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/145341-stock-electric-propeller-vehicle-showcase-bringing-power-to-the-people\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-21T06:53:22Z\u0022 title=\u002204/21/2017 06:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 21, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Reusables\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}